 To enable NCFETs with fast, low-hysteresis and low-power operation, following recommendations are proposed: (a) Scaling the interfacial SiO2 layer or replacing the interfacial SiO2 layer with high permittivity oxide to reduce the switching time as most of the voltage in MFIS stack could then be dropped across FE. (b) Developing sub-5 nm HZO films with lower coercive field to allow complete domain switching at lower voltages. (c) Sub-5 nm HZO films is expected to manifest lower polarization (due to the reduction in orthorhombic phase of HZO films as their thickness scales) that would help in naturally minimizing the hysteresis window in NCFETs (
\$\sim 2\text{P}_{r}/\text{C}_{FE}\$
) [6], [7].

